üëãüèº there‚Äôs something different about our Instagram‚Ä¶as you might know if you watched our stories or saw our profile yesterday! Jacob and I made the decision to remove his name from our page (don‚Äôt worry, he‚Äôs not going anywhere!). You‚Äôve seen our travels from my perspective for years now, and we wanted to be clear on who is really behind this account. If you follow along on finduslost.com, you know that I‚Äôm the one writing our travel guides and sharing pieces of our life abroad. We wanted to be consistent and honest with this update. Also, Instagram has changed, and so have we (but more on that in my latest blog post!).
We‚Äôve been talking about this for months and I‚Äôm excited to finally make it official. I shared all the reasons we decided to make this update, and what it means for us, on our blog. Including why we no longer wanted to be labeled as just a ‚Äòcouples account‚Äô. Give it a read - I‚Äôm honestly so curious to hear from you guys on this one! Link is in our profile!

We officially moved into our NYC apartment less than a week ago and I‚Äôm already falling for this city ‚ù§Ô∏èüèô It feels sooo amazing to be in one spot after non-stop travel for 8 months! Our plan is to have New York as our home base at least through summer...I can‚Äôt wait to explore more! 
Quick tips for the best views of NYC:
- Top of the Rock is the best, it has views of Central Park & the Empire State building.
- We went right at opening (8am) and it was perfect. No one around!
- Don‚Äôt miss the VERY top, there‚Äôs a small staircase leading up & that‚Äôs where this photo was taken from.
Thoughts on these tips? Save the post if you like them! Would love to start sharing more! 
Thank you for the snap @lusttilldawn üëêüèº

This year is about balance for us. My personal new year‚Äôs resolution is to keep up with my morning routine. I‚Äôve been writing down 3 things I‚Äôm grateful for every morning, and 3 items I‚Äôm going to accomplish each day in my @personalplanner. Here‚Äôs my 15-minute morning routine:
- Wake up (no phone!)
- 5-10 minutes of meditation
- Write 3 things I‚Äôm grateful for & 3 tasks to accomplish that day

DAY 5 of #finduslostflashbacks üåõ our favorite new destination of 2018‚Ä¶MILOS.
We celebrated our first-ever wedding anniversary on this beautiful island. It‚Äôs been an absolutely crazy year, between committing full-time to travel blogging, leaving our apartment in Amsterdam, and traveling more than ever before. Thankful every day for this guy by my side through all the ups, downs, life lessons, unforgettable moments, and pure happiness. 
I hope you ring in the new year with positivity and excitement for what‚Äôs to come. Something about 2019 feels like it‚Äôs going to be special..‚ô• Thanks for the constant love and support everyone! Cheers to an amazing new year ü•Ç

DAY 4 of #finduslostflashbacks üå¥ the beautiful, undiscovered Cook Islands.
What I see when someone mentions ‚Äòparadise‚Äô now‚Ä¶the jungles, crystal clear blue water, and landscapes of the Cook Islands. Jacob and I visited here in summer and went out one night to look for a viewpoint on Aitutaki island. We drove our rental car until the road ended and found a walking path up to the top (there was no one around, and we had no idea if we were in the right place). Just before the path leveled off I turned around to look back at this view and he snapped this photo. üí´ 
I rounded up our most-viewed and most-loved blog posts of 2018 on finduslost.com and our Cook Islands post made the top 5. You can see all the ones that made the list by clicking the link in our profile. Some good inspo in there for your 2019 travels!

DAY 3 of #finduslostflashbacks üá¨üá∑ we spent one week in Paros over the summer, with friends who flew in from all over the US and Europe. 
Each night we had our own ‚Äòbig fat Greek BBQ‚Äô, played games, and went out on the town. Each day we‚Äôd leave our house on our own ATV‚Äôs (we looked like a ridiculous biker gang) to find a new beach on the island. We took a ferry to Antiparos island one day to find a cliff jumping spot tucked away on the coast.
Somehow we had this place to ourselves, and it was one of the most beautiful swimming spots we‚Äôd ever seen. LOOK AT THAT WATER üò≥üòç if you search ‚ÄòParos‚Äô on finduslost.com you can see more from this island hopping trip! 
Convinced the Greek Islands is the best place in the world to host a friends trip...tag the friend (or friends!) who need to meet you here in 2019 üëáüèºüí¶

DAY 2 of #finduslostflashbacks üóù easily one of the most memorable trips we took this year was our trip to Beirut, Lebanon. We traveled here to learn about the most notable human rights issues taking place in the Middle East, including the ones frequently covered by the media and the ones left out. 
2018 was our year of saying yes - yes to new experiences, yes to taking on jobs, yes to traveling last minute. 2019 is going to be our year of balance. Balancing trips we take for ‚Äòwork‚Äô (though it still doesn‚Äôt quite feel like work!), with traveling for the sake of exploring. And hopefully, more trips to educate ourselves and share our experiences on timely issues around the world, from a first-hand perspective.
Balance is our one-word mantra heading into 2019! Share yours below, we all need a keyword going into this year‚Ä¶ üòâ

Looking back on 2018 - DAY 1 ‚õ∞
I‚Äôll be sharing some of our favorite photos and memories each day as we head into 2019, starting today with the Faroe Islands. 
The Faroes were on our bucket list for ages, ever since someone compared the landscapes there to Iceland. Traveling here felt like we had stepped back in time- there was no one taking photos around us, no one to ask for directions. We‚Äôd drive to a waterfall or a lookout we found a photo of and have to figure out ourselves how to get there. It was traveling as it should be (anyone else miss this kind of trip?).
Jacob took this photo of me after a hike, right before we turned around to head back. Its one of my favorites, as many of our unplanned ones tend to be. ‚ú® #finduslostflashbacks

Merry Christmas and Happy Holidays! We hope your days are filled with love, laughs, and lots of delicious holiday food ‚ù§Ô∏è here‚Äôs to an amazing rest of the year and start of 2019 (it‚Äôs going to be a good one!)

greetings from b e i r u t ‚ãÜ we‚Äôve been here the last few days with @humanrightswatch to educate ourselves on the most notable human rights issues taking place around the world ‚Äî both the ones reported on, and the ones often forgotten. 
Beirut is an incredible city, with a tumultuous history and lots of undiscovered gems (like this abandoned palace, damaged during the civil war). I wish I could share more photos from our trip, but honestly we spent most of our time indoors. The past few days we discussed the war in Syria and the conditions for refugees abroad, the disappearance of journalists trying to shed light on issues, we watched videos (I found the most interesting one to be a Human Rights Watch researcher leaving Gaza for the first time, which I linked in our stories), and more. 
Jacob introduced me to @humanrightswatch years ago and I felt the urge to share more about this part of our travels. Instagram isn‚Äôt the first place most will go to read about something like this, but it is our biggest audience and why I‚Äôve decided to share more about this trip. Check out our stories for more from our visit and leave us any questions in our stories or below. ‚ù§Ô∏è

‚Ä¢ one of the more amazing things traveling far from home can do is remind you that wherever you are, there is always a connection to home waiting to be found. For us, that was the other day when we stumbled upon our own taste of L.A. in Ljubljana. Some friends might have an idea of where Pop's Place in Slovenia transported us upon first bite (and for those of you who don't, ask us and we'll be happy to share the details). But we did a double take when we learned the owner, Greg, is a Newport Beach local-turned Slovenian restauranteur. It's a small world. And luckily a small city...because Pop's place was so good, it had us coming back for seconds.
